        THIS_VERIDICAL_CONFLUX_HERE_IS_A_LIFELINE_FOR                          = 7829,  -- This veridical conflux here is a lifeline for us survivors. At the touch of a hand, it'll instantaneously transport you to any other conflux with which you've had contact. As long as you have enough cruor to power it, that is.
        FOR_THE_SAKE_OF_QUICK_IDENTIFICATION_ALL_CONFLUXES                     = 7830,  -- For the sake of quick identification, all confluxes discovered in the area have been allocated numbers. The one at which I stand sentry is the first. Follow the highroad south, and you will eventually come by the second.
        NOW_IF_ONLY_THERE_WERE_A_CONFLUX_THAT                                  = 7831,  -- Now, if only there were a conflux that would take me back to my beloved Bastok...
        WELCOME_FRRRIEND_TO_THE_CENTRAL_ENCAMPMENT_SERVICED_BY                 = 7832,  -- Welcome, frrriend, to the central encampment, serviced by veridical conflux number fourrr. With the dependable LT-05 Martello buttressing the resistance effort, peace is rrrelatively well preserved in this area.
        THE_RAVINE_GRRRAVEN_LANDSCAPE_OF_LA_THEINE_PUTS                        = 7833,  -- The ravine-grrraven landscape of La Theine puts me in mind of my homeland... Oh, how I long for those bygone--what? Otherrr conflux locations, you ask? One's located near to a valley east of here, I believe.
        YOU_VE_DONE_WELL_TO_COME_THIS_FAR                                      = 7834,  -- You've done well to come this far. On behalf of our leader Halver, I welcome you to the southeastern encampment. The people here are conducting biological research on the Abyssean hordes, that we might develop countermeasures against them.
        WERE_YOU_PERCHANCE_ABLE_TO_LOCATE_THE_FIFTH                            = 7835,  -- Were you perchance able to locate the fifth veridical conflux as you journeyed here? Strike westward and you shall find it.
        SEE_YOU_THE_GLOWING_EMBLEM_TIS_CALLED_A                                = 7836,  -- See you the glowing emblem? 'Tis called a searing ward, a defensive barrier against hostile life-forms.
        YOU_SHAN_T_COME_TO_HARM_SO_LONG                                        = 7837,  -- You shan't come to harm so long as you remain within its protective sphere.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_BUSINESS_THAT_TAKES_YOU_BEYOND                             = 7838,  -- If you have business that takes you beyond the ward, however, you must first have visitant status issued. The conflux surveyor posted by the San d'Orian flag can tell you more about this.
        IF_YOU_VE_A_MIND_TO_OUTLIVE_YOUR                                       = 7839,  -- If you've a mind to outlive your peers, then heed my words. When engaged in combat with an Abyssean monster, you would be well advised to exploit its weakness.
        WHILE_MASSIVE_DAMAGE_MAY_NOT_BE_DEALT_IN                               = 7840,  -- While massive damage may not be dealt in so doing, you'll most likely succeed in impairing the movement and abilities of your foe.
        KNOW_ALSO_THAT_CHANGES_HAVE_BEEN_OBSERVED_TO                           = 7841,  -- Know also that changes have been observed to occur depending on your choice of killing blow. Do not be shy to experiment should the opportunity present itself.
        MY_LAST_PIECE_OF_ADVICE_YOU_MAY_CHOOSE                                 = 7842,  -- My last piece of advice, you may choose to ignore only at your peril: Abyssean monsters are drawn to commotion.
        A_BATTLE_THAT_RAGES_ON_IN_ONE_AREA                                     = 7843,  -- A battle that rages on in one area will for a certainty attract uninvited guests, each one stronger and deadlier than the last. If left unharassed for a time, however, the dreadful ones will grow bored and leave in search of better sport.
        BEHOLD_THE_METICULOUSLY_MAINTAINED_RECORD_OF_YOUR_EXPLOITS             = 7844,  -- Behold the meticulously maintained record of your exploits! Your progress for this area's objectives is thus:
        TIS_MY_PLEASURE_TO_CONFIRM_THE_COMPLETION_OF                           = 7845,  -- 'Tis my pleasure to confirm the completion of this objective! Huzzah!
        MY_WORD_YOU_VE_COMPLETED_ALL_THE_OBJECTIVES                            = 7846,  -- My word! You've completed all the objectives in this area! Truly exceptional!
        TIS_MY_UTMOST_PLEASURE_TO_PROFFER_YOU_THIS                             = 7847,  -- 'Tis my utmost pleasure to proffer you this as a small gesture of our appreciation for your efforts.
        FARE_YOU_WELL_ON_YOUR_JOURNEYS_UPON_THIS                               = 7848,  -- Fare you well on your journeys upon this wasteland of death.
        PSSST_YOU_THERE_AVE_YOU_GOT_ANY_CRUOR                                  = 7849,  -- Pssst, you there! 'Ave you got any cruor, now?
        GOT_CRUOR_DO_I_EVER_CRU_WHAT                                           = 7850,  -- Got cruor? Do I ever! Cru...what?
        YOU_NEW_ERE_I_GATHER_CRUOR_S_A                                         = 7851,  -- You new 'ere, I gather? Cruor's a type o' mineral what can be found as deposits on the beasties 'ere in Abyssea.
        THERE_S_SOME_AS_CALL_IT_BLOOD_GOLD                                     = 7852,  -- There's some as call it blood gold, an' small wonder. Brimmin' with energy these lil' red granules are, an' right useful for all sorts o' stuff.
        FOLK_EREABOUTS_USE_EM_IN_PLACE_O_COIN                                  = 7853,  -- Folk 'ereabouts use 'em in place o' coin nowadays, an' for travellin' through 'em periodical confluctional thingamabobs. Don't want t' be caught wiffout cruor, you don't.
        IF_YOU_VE_HOOKED_YOURSELF_UP_WIFF_SOME                                 = 7854,  -- If you've hooked yourself up wiff some, then you'll be wantin' to speak wiff a cruor prospector, you will.
        WHEN_THE_ABYSSEAN_HORDES_FIRST_APPEARED_A_MASSIVE                      = 7855,  -- When the Abyssean hordes first appeared, a massive whirlwind--or something similar as makes no difference--came and blew away all the people in San d'Oria as if they were rag dolls, myself included.
        ONE_MINUTE_I_WAS_TENDING_TO_AIRSHIP_PASSENGERS                         = 7856,  -- One minute I was tending to airship passengers. The next, waking up battered and bruised in La Theine.
        WHAT_IN_THE_WORLD_COULD_HAVE_HAPPENED_THAT                             = 7857,  -- What in the world could have happened that day? No one seems to have an explanation. <Sigh>... I wish I were back in Jeuno with my precious Albiona by my side...
        BESIDES_WHERE_YOU_STAND_TWO_OTHER_ENCAMPMENTS_HAVE                     = 7858,  -- Besides where you stand, two other encampments have been established in La Theine. 'Tis from these three locations that we survivors wage resistance against the Abyssean hordes.
        IF_YOU_SEEK_THE_CENTRAL_ENCAMPMENT_YOU_MUST                            = 7859,  -- If you seek the central encampment, you must first follow the mountains south. Beyond the first valley you will find two ponds, one large and one small. Nestled into the ravine north of there is where you will find your destination.
        THE_SOUTHEASTERN_ENCAMPMENT_CAN_EASILY_BE_REACHED_FROM                 = 7860,  -- The southeastern encampment can easily be reached from the central encampment. Simply strike for the plateau's easternmost edge, and thence follow the mountains south. The rest should be self-explanatory.
        FOR_THE_NONCE_TIS_ALL_WE_CAN_DO                                        = 7861,  -- For the nonce 'tis all we can do to stay alive. But mark my words, the Kingdom of San d'Oria shall rise from the ashes and purge the land of the foulness that corrupts it!
        OH_SUCH_A_BIND_I_VE_GOTTEN_MYSELF                                      = 7862,  -- Oh, such a bind I've gotten myself into... Ah, kind sir/madam]! Please hear my plight!
        AT_MY_SISTER_S_BEHEST_I_VE_COME                                        = 7863,  -- At my sister's behest I've come here to procure supplies, but alas, I was set upon by a vicious beast. I was able to drive it away, but not before taking a leg wound. Now I find I cannot hobble more than a few fulms without my leg giving out.
        WHILE_I_AM_LOATH_TO_ASK_THIS_OF                                        = 7864,  -- While I am loath to ask this of you, # must absolutely be delivered to my sister at the central encampment. I beg you, friend, won't you do me this simple favor?
        HELP_DELIVER_HOW_COULD_I_REFUSE_A_FRIEND                               = 7865,  -- Help deliver %? How could I refuse a friend? I'm not your friend.
        OH_WELL_THEN_I_LL_JUST_WAIT_AND                                        = 7866,  -- Oh. Well, then I'll just wait and pray that a selfless soul comes to my aid.
        THANK_YOU_KIND_SIR_MADAM_YOU_VE_NO                                     = 7867,  -- Thank you, kind sir/madam]! You've no idea how much this means to me! Please take this %--it should serve to ease the burden of harvesting.
        MY_SISTER_IS_CALLED_RUGIETTE_SHE_CAN_APPEAR                            = 7868,  -- My sister is called Rugiette. She can appear brusque at times, but deep down she is a sweetheart, truly.
        THAT_S_DELIVERED_TO_MY_SISTER_RUGIETTE_SHE                             = 7869,  -- That's # delivered to my sister, Rugiette. She awaits at the central encampment, which lies within a ravine by some ponds to the southeast.
        SIGH_IT_S_SO_TEDIOUS_HERE_INSIDE_THIS                                  = 7870,  -- <Sigh> It's so tedious here inside this proverbial hole in the ground, but I suppose this won't kill me near as quickly as being out and about...
        HM_WHY_THESE_ARE_THE_SUPPLIES_MY_SISTER                                = 7871,  -- Hm? Why, these are the supplies my sister was supposed to fetch...
        YOU_HAVE_MY_GRATITUDE_KIND_SIR_MADAM_BUT                               = 7872,  -- You have my gratitude, kind sir/madam]...but how is it that you're making the delivery instead?
        OH_NEVER_MIND_DOUBTLESS_REGINE_IS_BEING_HER                            = 7873,  -- Oh, never mind. Doubtless Regine is being her usual lazy self and asked a hapless passerby to do her chores. Should you meet her again, do chide her on my behalf.
        I_KNEW_I_WAS_RIGHT_TO_DEPEND_ON                                        = 7874,  -- I knew I was right to depend on you! You have my gratitude! Now the folk of the encampment need not go without.
        OH_FANCY_MEETING_YOU_HERE_AGAIN_I_M                                    = 7875,  -- Oh, fancy meeting you here again. I'm still unable walk, would you believe it? Would you perchance, um...have spare time to make another delivery in my stead?
        HM_YOURS_BE_A_FRESH_FACE_TO_THESE                                      = 7876,  -- Hm? Yours be a fresh face to these parts, if my flounderin' memory's not mistaken. And what's a newcomer good for if he/she] can't be prevailed upon for a chore or three? Ohohoho...
        NOT_THAT_YE_BE_NEEDIN_TELLIN_BUT_THE                                   = 7877,  -- Not that ye be needin' tellin', but the folk here have their hands full with just stayin' alive. And then there's the bloody-red sky loomin' above...
        THE_SUN_S_UP_AND_DISAPPEARED_LIKE_A                                    = 7878,  -- The sun's up and disappeared, like a regular Lothario. The moon shines bright as ever, to be sure, but folk can't live long without sunlight before they start goin' pale and pallid. That's why I've been makin' a special medicine--a supplement for sunlight, ye could say.
        I_VE_FAIR_RUN_OUT_OF_THE_I                                             = 7879,  -- I've fair run out of the % I use to brew my medicine. Would ye be a dear and fetch one for old Amaura?
        FETCH_FOR_AMAURA_ALWAYS_WILLING_TO_SERVE_I                             = 7880,  -- Fetch % for Amaura? Always willing to serve! I've better things to do, lady.
        IS_THAT_RIGHT_YOUNG_UNS_THESE_DAYS_HAVE                                = 7881,  -- Is that right... Young'uns these days have lost all respect for their elders, 'twould seem.
        THANK_YE_MUCHLY_YOUNG_MAN_LADY_NOW_YE                                  = 7882,  -- Thank ye muchly, young man/lady]. Now, ye'll be wantin' to go to the edge of the ravine east of here, when the moon's not showin' its great round face, mind ye.
        FROM_YOUR_VANTAGE_POINT_LOOK_DOWN_INTO_THE                             = 7883,  -- From your vantage point, look down into the valley floor. Find a gentle glow and ye'll find what we need.
        IT_JUST_SO_HAPPENS_THAT_MY_YOUNG_APPRENTICE                            = 7884,  -- It just so happens that my young apprentice, Raminel, is on-site at this very moment. Follow his instructions, and with a wee bit of pluck, ye'll have the % before ye know it.
        AH_YE_VE_RETURNED_AND_WITH_WHAT_I                                      = 7885,  -- Ah, ye've returned...and with what I asked for, no less! I knew ye had potential, young man/lady].
        THANKS_TO_YE_THE_FOLK_HERE_CAN_KEEP                                    = 7886,  -- Thanks to ye, the folk here can keep enjoyin' ruddy complexions even without sunlight. Here's a little something for your troubles. It ought to come in handy.
        SO_YE_VE_RETURNED_AND_WITHOUT_WHAT_I                                   = 7887,  -- So ye've returned...and without what I asked for. Looks like it'll take one with a backbone firmer than yours to fetch what I need.
        WELL_WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_THE_TRUSTY                                       = 7888,  -- Well, well, if it isn't the trusty young man/lady]. My thanks for the other day.
        HM_BUT_WHY_THE_LONG_FACE_I_HAVE                                        = 7889,  -- Hm? But why the long face? I have just the chore to perk ye right up!
        AH_AMAURA_SENT_YOU_I_LL_WAGER_RAMINEL                                  = 7890,  -- Ah, Amaura sent you, I'll wager. Raminel is my name, and I thank you for your aid.
        WITHOUT_ADO_I_SHALL_EXPLAIN_THE_PROCESS                                = 7891,  -- Without ado, I shall explain the process.
        I_HAVE_WITH_ME_A_ROPE_MAGICKED_TO                                      = 7892,  -- I have with me a rope, magicked to be elastic yet durable. One end of it I shall tie to the tree yonder, and the other to your ankles.
        AFTER_THAT_ALL_THAT_S_REQUIRED_OF_YOU                                  = 7893,  -- After that, all that's required of you is to dive into the ravine and grab the %. It's as simple as running parcels. Just give the word and we'll get started.
        ARE_YOU_READY_READY_TO_THE_EXTREME_I                                   = 7894,  -- Are you ready? Ready to the extreme! I hear my kettle whistling...
        AH_YES_THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT                                               = 7895,  -- Ah yes, that's the spirit.
        SIMPLY_DIVE_DOWN_AND_GRAB_HOLD_OF_THE                                  = 7896,  -- Simply dive down and grab hold of the % when it's within reach. Let us commence!
        ONE                                                                    = 7897,  -- One!
        TWO                                                                    = 7898,  -- Two!
        THREE                                                                  = 7899,  -- Three!
        DESCEND                                                                = 7900,  -- Descend!
        GRAB_THE_TRIES_LEFT_NOW                                                = 7901,  -- Grab the %... (Tries left: #) Now!
        BEAUTIFULLY_DONE_I_HAD_EVERY_CONFIDENCE_THAT_YOU                       = 7902,  -- Beautifully done! I had every confidence that you would succeed!
        AMAURA_AWAITS_YOU_AT_THE_ENCAMPMENT_PLEASE_HURRY                       = 7903,  -- Amaura awaits you at the encampment. Please hurry back.
        OH_THAT_WAS_SO_AWFULLY_CLOSE_WOULD_YOU                                 = 7904,  -- Oh, that was so awfully close! Would you care for another attempt?
        HMMM_PERHAPS_WE_CAN_DO_WITHOUT_ROSY_CHEEKS                             = 7905,  -- Hmmm...perhaps we can do without rosy cheeks for a day or two. And I would sooner not dive for your broken corpse.
        JUMPS_FAILURES                                                         = 7906,  -- Jumps: # Failures: #
        THERE_S_SOMETHING_FOUL_IN_THE_AIR_OF                                   = 7907,  -- There's something foul in the air of late. Can you not feel it? Dark times have befallen us, yes, but this is something else altogether. This is...the true darkness.
        COULD_IT_BE_THAT_I_AM_THE_ONLY                                         = 7908,  -- Could it be that I am the only soul who senses this wickedness...?
        I_MUST_HAVE_A_CHARM_TO_WARD_AWAY                                       = 7909,  -- I must have a charm to ward away this ultimate evil.
        SUCH_A_CHARM_WOULD_NEED_TO_BE_MADE                                     = 7910,  -- Such a charm would need to be made of # ...
        MIGHT_YOU_BRING_ME_THE_MATERIALS_I_REQUIRE                             = 7911,  -- Might you bring me the materials I require?
        WILL_YOU_GATHER_THE_MATERIALS_AS_WELL_AS                               = 7912,  -- Will you gather the materials? As well as some for myself! I don't think so...
        I_AM_IN_YOUR_DEBT_I_MUST_HAVE                                          = 7913,  -- I am in your debt! I must have them to ward away the darkness... Remember, I need # !
        YOU_DO_NOT_SHARE_MY_FEAR_WHILE_WE                                      = 7914,  -- You do not share my fear... While we stand here debating, the true darkness creeps ever closer! I must do something!
        MY_CHARM_REQUIRES_MAKE_HASTE                                           = 7915,  -- My charm requires # ... Make haste!
        THANK_YOU_THIS_SHOULD_HOLD_THE_DARKNESS_AT                             = 7916,  -- Thank you! This should hold the darkness at bay...if only for a while. Bring more, if you can.
        I_MUST_HAVE_MORE_CHARMS_PLEASE_BRING_ME                                = 7917,  -- I must have more charms! Please, bring me sets of # !
        I_PROMISE_YOU_SHALL_NOT_LEAVE_EMPTY_HANDED                             = 7918,  -- I promise you shall not leave empty-handed!
        ID_7919                                                                = 7919,  -- ......
        WELL_PINCH_MY_CHEEKS_AND_CALL_ME_SENILE                                = 7920,  -- Well, pinch my cheeks and call me senile! If it isn't %!
        I_M_PLEASED_TO_SEE_THAT_YOUNG_HALVER                                   = 7921,  -- I'm pleased to see that young Halver's efforts've finally borne fruit. Now we can only pray that the medicine serves its purpose.
        AND_THERE_S_ONLY_ONE_WAY_TO_FIND                                       = 7922,  -- And there's only one way to find out...
        FEELIN_ANY_BETTER_YOUNG_LADY_HAVE_YE_FINALLY                           = 7923,  -- Feelin' any better, young lady? Have ye finally come back to us?
        HMM                                                                    = 7924,  -- ...Hmm?
        WH_WHAT_AM_I_WHERE_RE_ALL                                              = 7925,  -- Wh-what am I... Where're all...
        GASP                                                                   = 7926,  -- <Gasp>!
        TH_THE_WORLD_IS_BEING_WATCHED                                          = 7927,  -- Th-the world is being watched!
        FROM_A_PLACE_FAR_BEYOND_MORTAL_REACH_BY                                = 7928,  -- From a place far beyond mortal reach...by eyes intent and forbidding...
        EH_I_M_AFRAID_ALL_OF_WHAT_YE                                           = 7929,  -- Eh? I'm afraid all of what ye just said went right over my head. Mind puttin' it in simpler terms for old Amaura?
        I_I_KNOW_NOT_HOW_I_VE_COME                                             = 7930,  -- I-I know not how I've come to possess this knowledge... Could it be...when I came in contact with that creature?
        YOU_ARE_HE_SHE_WHO_BROUGHT_ME_THE                                      = 7931,  -- You are he/she] who brought me the medicine, correct? I would ask another boon of you.
        THE_VILE_CREATURE_THAT_TOOK_MY_EYE_IS                                  = 7932,  -- The vile creature that took my eye is a gnole known as Lugarhoo. I ask that you be my blade of retribution and slay it, and deliver me its left eye as proof of the deed.
        GIFT_ME_WITH_THE_CLOSURE_I_SEEK_AND                                    = 7933,  -- Gift me with the closure I seek, and in return I shall entrust to you my %.
        ITS_POWER_IS_FAR_BEYOND_ONE_OF_MY                                      = 7934,  -- Its power is far beyond one of my modest capacity, but in your hands I sense that great feats shall be accomplished.
        AVENGE_CURILLA_S_LEFT_EYE_THAT_MANGY_GNOLE                             = 7935,  -- Avenge Curilla's left eye? That mangy gnole will pay! I'd sooner not get involved.
        THEN_WE_HAVE_NAUGHT_LEFT_TO_DISCUSS_LEAVE                              = 7936,  -- ...Then we have naught left to discuss. Leave me in peace.
        AWWW_YE_MUSTN_T_GIVE_UP_YOUNG_LADY                                     = 7937,  -- Awww, ye mustn't give up, young lady. Why, ye're the one who's brought so much hope to all of us here!
        I_BEG_YE_TO_RECONSIDER_WON_T_YE                                        = 7938,  -- I beg ye to reconsider. Won't ye do this lil' favor for poor Curilla?
        THIS_MEANS_MORE_TO_ME_THAN_YOU_KNOW                                    = 7939,  -- This means more to me than you know. Thank you. We've known each other for but a moment, yet I feel that uncommon courage emanates from you.
        BE_WARNED_THAT_LUGARHOO_IS_NO_ORDINARY_GNOLE                           = 7940,  -- Be warned that Lugarhoo is no ordinary gnole and shan't be felled with ease. I pray for your safety and success.
        INCREDIBLE_YOU_TRULY_DEFEATED_LUGARHOO_YOUR_POTENTIAL_KNOWS            = 7941,  -- Incredible! You truly defeated Lugarhoo! Your potential knows no bounds, 'twould seem.
        THANKS_TO_YOU_MY_HEART_MAY_BE_AT                                       = 7942,  -- Thanks to you, my heart may be at peace once more. Here is the % I promised. May it serve you well.
        MY_FERVENT_DESIRE_FOR_REVENGE_HAD_DIVESTED_ME                          = 7943,  -- My fervent desire for revenge had divested me of my manners, but now I would know the name of my champion.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_NAME_I_AM_KNOWN_AS                                        = 7944,  -- What is your name? I am known as %. My identity is of no import.
        THAT_IS_A_NAME_I_SHALL_NEVER_FORGET                                    = 7945,  -- %... That is a name I shall never forget. I beseech you. Please stand by my people and I as we continue our journey through this darkest of valleys.
        YOU_ARE_AS_MODEST_AS_YOU_ARE_VALIANT                                   = 7946,  -- You are as modest as you are valiant, %. I beseech you. Please stand by my people and I as we continue our journey through this darkest of valleys.
        CONFOUND_IT_YET_ANOTHER_FAILURE_WHAT_IN_THIS                           = 7947,  -- Confound it, yet another failure! What in this accursed world am I to do now?
        NOT_MOMENTS_AFTER_WE_RECEIVED_THIS_FOR_REPAIRS                         = 7948,  -- Not moments after we received this % for repairs, some foul fiends did for our resident craftsman. Heaven knows I've tried to mend it for days now, but 'tis no use. I simply have not the expertise.
        WITH_TIMES_DIFFICULT_AS_THEY_ARE_NAUGHT_CAN                            = 7949,  -- With times difficult as they are, naught can be permitted to go to waste. Even a humble fishing rod could well spell the difference between a belly full of fish and starvation...but I'm at my wit's end.
        WHAT_WILL_DO_YOU_NOTHING_CHEER_HIM_UP                                  = 7950,  -- What will do you? Nothing. Cheer him up with a jest. Offer to mend the fishing rod.
        WHY_DID_THE_FUNGUAR_CROSS_THE_HIGHROAD_YOU                             = 7951,  -- Why did the funguar cross the highroad, you say!? Egads, man/woman], what manner of sick fool are you? This is no time for jests!
        YOU_WOULD_MEND_THE_FISHING_ROD_FOR_ME                                  = 7952,  -- You would mend the fishing rod for me? My thanks, kind sir/madam]! You are a true friend to the people!
        HERE_IS_THE_THAT_REQUIRES_ATTENTION_ONCE_IT                            = 7953,  -- Here is the % that requires attention. Once it is repaired, please deliver it to my brother, Gallijaux, who is based at the southeastern encampment.
        THE_ROAD_THAT_LEADS_THERE_IS_FRAUGHT_WITH                              = 7954,  -- The road that leads there is fraught with danger, yet it is a journey that must be made for the greater good. The day each of us ceases to do our part is the day mankind perishes from the world. Do I not speak the truth?
        AFTER_YOU_VE_REPAIRED_THE_PLEASE_SEE_IT                                = 7955,  -- After you've repaired the %, please see it delivered safely to my brother, Gallijaux. He can be found at the southeastern encampment.
        BROTHER_FANCIES_HIMSELF_AN_ACCOMPLISHED_ANGLER_BUT_THE                 = 7956,  -- Brother fancies himself an accomplished angler, but the rate at which he breaks fishing rods speaks otherwise. And as he shows no sign of improvement, there's precious little I can do save polish my own mending skills.
        AH_YOU_COULDN_T_HAVE_COME_AT_A                                         = 7957,  -- Ah, you couldn't have come at a better time. Yet another fishing rod has fallen victim to my brother's ineptitude, you see, and I haven't quite mastered the repairs...
        BEFORE_THE_WORLD_AS_WE_KNEW_IT_WAS                                     = 7958,  -- Before the world as we knew it was laid to waste, the fierce rivalry Gallijaux and Joulet shared as anglers used to vex me to no end. But looking back now, those days were a blessing from the heavens. Would that we could learn to appreciate what we have before they're taken away...
        WHY_IS_IT_TAKING_SO_LONG_TO_MEND                                       = 7959,  -- Why is it taking so long to mend a simple fishing rod? The poor folk here are soon like to die of starvation...
        WHY_THIS_IS_THE_I_HAD_SENT_TO                                          = 7960,  -- Why, this is the % I had sent to be repaired!
        I_HAD_BEEN_EXPECTING_THE_CRAFTSMAN_S_FAMILIAR                          = 7961,  -- I had been expecting the craftsman's familiar face, but doubtless he's swamped with repair work.
        PRAY_SEND_MY_REGARDS_TO_MY_LITTLE_BROTHER                              = 7962,  -- Pray send my regards to my little brother when next you see him.
        NOW_THAT_THE_TOOL_OF_MY_TRADE_IS                                       = 7963,  -- Now that the tool of my trade is returned to me, I had best return to my duty. 'Tis a weighty responsibility, ensuring that all mouths are fed.
        HM_AN_OUTSIDER_ARE_WE_I_VE_NO                                          = 7964,  -- Hm? An outsider, are we? I've no time to waste on one who's yet to earn my trust. Begone with you.
        AH_YOU_MUST_BE_THE_NEWCOMER_FOLK_VE                                    = 7965,  -- Ah, you must be the newcomer folk've been bending my ears about. I am Fontoumant. Before this evil engulfed us, I had a respected post overseeing the Consortium's warehouses.
        BUT_THAT_AND_MORE_WERE_TAKEN_AWAY_FROM                                 = 7966,  -- But that and more were taken away from me, and I have those Abyssean fiends to thank for it.
        MY_SMOLDERING_DESIRE_TO_EXACT_REVENGE_UPON_THE                         = 7967,  -- My smoldering desire to exact revenge upon the vile creatures is all that drives me now. I spend my days devising ways to exterminate them, and painfully. Such is my joy.
        I_HAD_A_SUSPICION_THAT_THE_CREATURES_APPEARANCE                        = 7968,  -- I had a suspicion that the creatures' appearance was connected to the increase in seismic activity, and the research I subsequently conducted lent credence to this theory.
        THE_FIENDS_SURGE_OUT_FROM_FISSURES_WOUNDS_ON                           = 7969,  -- The fiends surge out from fissures--wounds on the earth's surface--that have opened up in ravines after tremors, I'm sure of it. I've a mind to delve deeper into this, but I require the assistance of one with a stout heart and a strong back.
        ASSIST_WITH_THE_RESEARCH_I_M_AT_YOUR                                   = 7970,  -- Assist with the research? I'm at your disposal! I've prior, less dangerous engagements.
        ACH_JUST_LIKE_THE_YEARLINGS_I_GET_EVERY                                = 7971,  -- Ach, just like the yearlings I get every day, you are. Away with you until you're willing to assist my research!
        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_THERE_MAY_BE_SOME                                    = 7972,  -- That's the spirit! There may be some hope for your generation yet. Now, let us dispense with the pleasantries as every moment spent in idleness could mean another score of demons being spawned into our midst.
        I_HAVE_CREATED_ANTI_ABYSSEAN_GRENADES_AND_I                            = 7973,  -- I have created anti-Abyssean grenades, and I would have you test them out at three newly opened fissures. The first is a stone's throw away from this encampment, and the second and third are located in the ravine west of here.
        IN_SHORT_YOU_ARE_TO_TAKE_THE_GRENADES                                  = 7974,  -- In short, you are to take the grenades and cast one into each fissure. Remarkably straightforward, wouldn't you say so?
        THE_FINDINGS_WILL_AVAIL_US_ONLY_IF_THE                                 = 7975,  -- The findings will avail us only if the experiment is conducted periodically, however, so I would thank you for your continued assistance. Now, off you go then!
        HM_FORGOTTEN_THE_FISSURE_LOCATIONS_HAVE_YOU_THE                        = 7976,  -- Hm? Forgotten the fissure locations, have you? The first is a stone's throw away from this encampment, and the second and third are located in the ravine west of here.
        AH_YOU_RE_BACK_I_TRUST_THE_TASK                                        = 7977,  -- Ah, you're back. I trust the task posed no difficulties. Take this as recompense for your troubles, and seek me here whenever you wish to assist further in my research.
        AH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_VERY_KIND_OF                                         = 7978,  -- Ah, it's you again. Very kind of you to show, but I've yet to finish readying another set of grenades. Return here in a while, if you would.
        AH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_THE_RESEARCH_CONTINUES                               = 7979,  -- Ah, it's you again. The research continues to yield useful data, in no small part thanks to you. I've just finished readying a new set of grenades. Might I prevail upon you to assist me again?
        YOU_SEE_AN_OMINOUS_FISSURE_ON_THE_RAVINE                               = 7980,  -- You see an ominous fissure on the ravine floor...
        CAST_INTO_IT_ATTACK_THE_DARKNESS_NOT_JUST                              = 7981,  -- Cast % into it? Attack the darkness! Not just yet.
        CASTS_INTO_THE_FISSURE                                                 = 7982,  -- % casts % into the fissure.
        THE_ANTI_ABYSSEAN_GRENADE_SCORES_A_CRITICAL_HIT                        = 7983,  -- The anti-Abyssean grenade scores a critical hit! The unidentified creature takes 9999 points of damage.
        DEFEATS_THE_UNIDENTIFIED_CREATURE                                      = 7984,  -- % defeats the unidentified creature.
        YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_USED_AN_ANTI_ABYSSEAN_GRENADE                         = 7985,  -- You have already used an anti-Abyssean grenade here.
        YOU_HAVE_USED_UP_ALL_YOUR_ANTI_ABYSSEAN                                = 7986,  -- You have used up all your anti-Abyssean grenades. Hasten back to the central encampment and report to Fontoumant.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_HAD_THE_DISPLEASURE_OF_MEETING                           = 7987,  -- Have you ever had the displeasure of meeting an Abyssean monster in battle? Those creatures strike with such fell force, a man's like to be knocked clean out of his armor if not unconscious.
        THE_RATE_OF_WEAR_AND_TEAR_EXPERIENCED_BY                               = 7988,  -- The rate of wear and tear experienced by equipment used in our struggle is staggering, and keeping our soldiers fitted with battle-worthy gear is proving to be a right royal headache. Consequently, we've had no choice but to explore, shall we say, unconventional means of replenishing arms and armor.
        IN_LA_THEINE_THERE_EXIST_FOUR_PONDS_EACH                               = 7989,  -- In La Theine there exist four ponds, each said to be the final resting place of many a fallen soldier. It follows that within them sleeps a veritable treasure trove of equipment, aged yet still serviceable.
        I_AM_LOATH_TO_DISTURB_THE_DEAD_IN                                      = 7990,  -- I am loath to disturb the dead in their sleep, yet our plight grows desperate. And as erstwhile warriors themselves, surely they would not begrudge us the arms we so direly need.
        AND_SHOULD_YOU_FISH_UP_ANY_OF_THESE                                    = 7991,  -- %, %, %, and %... Should you fish up any of these items, I ask that you bring them to me.
        WHILE_I_AM_NOT_POSSESSED_OF_ANY_GREAT                                  = 7992,  -- While I am not possessed of any great smithing skill, many years as an avid collector has taught me a thing or two of maintenance and restoration.
        AH_YOU_VE_BROUGHT_ME_YOU_HAVE_MY                                       = 7993,  -- Ah, you've brought me %. You have my thanks.
        THIS_SHOULD_KEEP_OUR_SOLDIERS_FROM_HAVING_TO                           = 7994,  -- This should keep our soldiers from having to charge into battle with naught but their smallclothes...if only for a while.
        FOR_NOW_PLEASE_ACCEPT_THIS_AS_A_SMALL                                  = 7995,  -- For now, please accept this as a small token of my gratitude. Should you fish up any more equipment, I ask you to bring them to me with all haste. Lives are depending on it.
        I_M_THANKFUL_FOR_THE_AID_YOU_VE                                        = 7996,  -- I'm thankful for the aid you've afforded us. Yet our struggles are never-ending, and our need for equipment ever dire.
        SHOULD_YOU_FISH_UP_ANY_MORE_OR_BRING                                   = 7997,  -- Should you fish up any more %, %, %, or %, bring them to me with all haste. I shall see to it that they are restored to battle-ready condition.
        WELCOME_FRIEND_TO_THE_SOUTHEASTERN_ENCAMPMENT_STAY_A                   = 7998,  -- Welcome, friend, to the southeastern encampment. Stay a while and rest your travel-weary body and mind at this enclave of survivors.
        WELCOME_FRIEND_TO_THE_SOUTHEASTERN_ENCAMPMENT_I_WOULD                  = 7999,  -- Welcome, friend, to the southeastern encampment. I would proffer you drink to slake your thirst, but our water source--the four ponds of La Theine--has become contaminated ever since the Abyssean creatures appeared.
        I_HAVE_ENDEAVORED_LONG_TO_CLEANSE_THE_PONDS                            = 8000,  -- I have endeavored long to cleanse the ponds that the folk might have access to potable water, but this undertaking has proven far too onerous to be borne by a single man.
        MIGHT_I_ENTREAT_YOUR_COOPERATION_IN_THIS_ENDEAVOR                      = 8001,  -- Might I entreat your cooperation in this endeavor, friend?
        OFFER_MIAGEAU_YOUR_COOPERATION_I_SURELY_WILL_POTABLE                   = 8002,  -- Offer Miageau your cooperation? I surely will. Potable water is overrated.
        IT_GRIEVES_ME_TO_SEE_THAT_THERE_ARE                                    = 8003,  -- It grieves me to see that there are still those who choose not to part ways with their selfishness.
        A_NOBLE_SOUL_SUCH_AS_YOURS_IS_SELDOM                                   = 8004,  -- A noble soul such as yours is seldom seen in these dark times. Blessings be upon you.
        I_ENTRUST_TO_YOU_THESE_FOUR_VIALS_OF                                   = 8005,  -- I entrust to you these four vials of chemicals. Take them and empty the contents of one into each of the four ponds.
        HAVING_ACCOMPLISHED_THAT_I_ASK_YOU_TO_DRAW                             = 8006,  -- Having accomplished that, I ask you to draw water samples using the selfsame vials and thence bring them back to me. Go with blessed speed, friend.
        I_HAVE_AWAITED_YOUR_RETURN_I_SHALL_TAKE                                = 8007,  -- I have awaited your return. I shall take the water samples off your hands.
        AH_TWOULD_APPEAR_THAT_WATER_QUALITY_HAS_IMPROVED                       = 8008,  -- Ah, 'twould appear that water quality has improved noticeably. You have done the surviving folk a great service, friend.
        THE_COMING_OF_THIS_CATACLYSM_HAS_SHAKEN_THE                            = 8009,  -- The coming of this cataclysm has shaken the people's faith. Many are those who believe that the world has been forsaken, but nothing could be further from the truth.
        THIS_IS_BUT_A_TRIAL_SENT_FROM_THE                                      = 8010,  -- This is but a trial sent from the heavens that we must together overcome.
        MAY_PARADISE_OPEN_ITS_GATES_TO_YOU                                     = 8011,  -- May Paradise open its gates to you.
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_ASSISTANCE_THE_DAY_PAST                             = 8012,  -- Thank you for your assistance the day past, friend. Yet with the Abyssean creatures still running rampant, the ponds do not remain cleansed for long. Might I entreat your aid once more?
        THE_WATER_APPEARS_MURKY_AND_STAGNATED                                  = 8013,  -- The water appears murky and stagnated...
        USE_THE_YES_NO_2                                                       = 8014,  -- Use the %? Yes. No.
        EMPTIES_INTO_THE_POND                                                  = 8015,  -- % empties % into the pond.
        THE_MURKINESS_OF_THE_WATER_HAS_SUBSIDED                                = 8016,  -- The murkiness of the water has subsided.
        DRAWS_A_SAMPLE_OF_WATER_WITH_AN_EMPTY                                  = 8017,  -- % draws a sample of water with an empty vial.
        YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_PURIFY_THIS_POND                                    = 8018,  -- You do not need to purify this pond further.
        YOU_HAVE_USED_UP_ALL_THE_VIALS_OF                                      = 8019,  -- You have used up all the vials of purification agent. Hasten back to the southeastern encampment and report to Miageau.
        BLESSEDLY_MY_HUSBAND_AND_I_HAVE_MANAGED_TO                             = 8020,  -- Blessedly, my husband and I have managed to survive together. But each time he leaves on patrol, I'm racked with anxiety that he may never return...heaven forfend.
        HIS_PROMISE_TO_STAY_IN_REGULAR_CONTACT_VIA                             = 8021,  -- His promise to stay in regular contact via linkpearl is all that sustains me. Speaking of which, I'm expecting a call at any moment now...
        OH_WHAT_AM_I_TO_DO_MY_HUSBAND                                          = 8022,  -- Oh, what am I to do? My husband is on patrol, and it's well past the time I'm supposed to hear from him.
        BEING_THE_SCATTERBRAIN_THAT_HE_IS_I_M                                  = 8023,  -- Being the scatterbrain that he is, I'm praying that he has merely misplaced his linkpearl. But there'll be no peace for me unless I find out for certain.
        COULD_I_TROUBLE_YOU_TO_DELIVER_THIS_TO                                 = 8024,  -- Could I trouble you to deliver this % to him?
        I_D_SEEK_HIM_OUT_MYSELF_TO_BE                                          = 8025,  -- I'd seek him out myself, to be sure, but I'm not made for the savage wilderness that has overtaken La Theine.
        DELIVER_THE_LINKPEARL_OF_COURSE_I_WILL_NOT                             = 8026,  -- Deliver the linkpearl? Of course I will. Not right now.
        Y_YOU_WON_T_BUT_MY_HUSBAND_MIGHT                                       = 8027,  -- Y-you won't? But...my husband might be d-dying...<sniffle>...in a ditch somewhere...<sob>...
        I_CANNOT_THANK_YOU_ENOUGH_MY_HUSBAND_S                                 = 8028,  -- I cannot thank you enough! My husband's name is Aaveleon.
        HE_SHOULD_BE_PATROLLING_LA_THEINE_AS_WE                                = 8029,  -- He should be patrolling La Theine as we speak. Please hurry, or I fear I shall lose my mind!
        I_WAS_ABLE_TO_REGAIN_CONTACT_WITH_MY                                   = 8030,  -- I was able to regain contact with my husband again. Thank you so much!
        THE_WORLD_MAY_NEVER_AGAIN_KNOW_PEACE_AND                               = 8031,  -- The world may never again know peace and tranquility. But for the sake of our loved ones, we must ever hold on to hope.
        FORGIVE_ME_BUT_I_M_IN_THE_MIDST                                        = 8032,  -- Forgive me, but I'm in the midst of patrol duty. And if you have a care for your life, I suggest you make for the safety of the encampment with all speed.
        WHY_THIS_IS_I_HAD_BEEN_BROODING_OVER                                   = 8033,  -- Why, this is %! I had been brooding over the one I misplaced the exact moment you showed up. My deepest thanks.
        AH_IT_WORKS_LIKE_A_CHARM_MY_WIFE                                       = 8034,  -- Ah, it works like a charm. My wife just responded to my call. Pray excuse me for a moment...
        THANKS_FOR_THE_LINKPEARL_MY_TURTLE_DOVE                                = 8035,  -- Thanks for the linkpearl, my turtle dove.
        ALL_IS_WELL_WITH_ME_REST_ASSURED_EVEN                                  = 8036,  -- All is well with me, rest assured. Even should I encounter a hellspawned beast, your ointment would mend my wounds in an instant.
        I_HEAR_YOU_SWEETLING_I_PROMISE_TO_BE                                   = 8037,  -- I hear you, sweetling. I promise to be ever cautious, for the sake our of children.
        I_SHALL_BE_WITH_YOU_SOON_STAY_SAFE                                     = 8038,  -- I shall be with you soon. Stay safe, apple of my eye.
        NOW_I_MAY_CONTINUE_MY_PATROL_WITH_AN                                   = 8039,  -- Now I may continue my patrol with an easier heart. You have done me a great kindness, friend.
        A_FEROCIOUS_RABBIT_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_GAMBOLS_IN                   = 8040,  -- A ferocious rabbit of immense proportions gambols in these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_FRENZIED_TIGER_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_PROWLS_THESE                   = 8041,  -- A frenzied tiger of immense proportions prowls these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_SAVAGE_BIRD_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_FLUTTERS_ABOUT                    = 8042,  -- A savage bird of immense proportions flutters about in these parts. Best maintain at a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_VICIOUS_BEE_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_DRONES_ABOUT                      = 8043,  -- A vicious bee of immense proportions drones about in these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_SINISTER_SPIRIT_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_HAUNTS_THESE                  = 8044,  -- A sinister spirit of immense proportions haunts these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        PIXIES_ONE_LARGE_AND_ONE_QUEENLY_FLIT_ABOUT                            = 8045,  -- Pixies--one large and one queenly--flit about in these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_HULKING_GIGAS_OF_UNPARALLELED_STRENGTH_LUMBERS_ABOUT                 = 8046,  -- A hulking Gigas of unparalleled strength lumbers about these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        A_FEARSOME_GNOLE_OF_IMMENSE_PROPORTIONS_STALKS_THESE                   = 8047,  -- A fearsome gnole of immense proportions stalks these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        BESIDES_AN_OBNOXIOUS_FLY_A_CRAB_OF_IMMENSE                             = 8048,  -- Besides an obnoxious fly, a crab of immense proportions scuttles about these parts. Best maintain a respectful distance, lest you have a death wish.
        I_SHALL_RESUME_MY_DUTY_GO_SAFELY_FRIEND                                = 8049,  -- I shall resume my duty. Go safely, friend.
        HM_I_HAVE_NO_BREATH_TO_WASTE_ON                                        = 8050,  -- Hm? I have no breath to waste on indolent outsiders. Begone from my sight this instant.
        YOUR_SELFLESS_DEEDS_ON_BEHALF_OF_THE_SURVIVOR                          = 8051,  -- Your selfless deeds on behalf of the survivor community have done much to forward our cause, so I'm told. Now my turn is come to entreat your assistance. Will you hear my plea?
        HEAR_HIS_PLEA_I_M_ALL_EARS_NOT                                         = 8052,  -- Hear his plea? I'm all ears. Not interested, sorry.
        HMPH_IT_APPEARS_THE_TALES_OF_YOUR_VALOR                                = 8053,  -- Hmph. It appears the tales of your valor were unfounded.
        YOU_HAVE_MY_BOUNDLESS_GRATITUDE_NOW_THEN_KNOW                          = 8054,  -- You have my boundless gratitude! Now then, know you of a woman called Curilla presently in convalescence at the northern encampment?
        DO_YOU_KNOW_CURILLA_I_SURELY_DO_CURA                                   = 8055,  -- Do you know Curilla? I surely do. Cura...who?
        TO_CALL_HER_THE_STONE_UPON_WHICH_SAN                                   = 8056,  -- To call her the stone upon which San d'Oria's proud order of Temple Knights is built would be no exaggeration.
        WERE_IT_NOT_FOR_CURILLA_S_INSPIRING_FORTITUDE                          = 8057,  -- Were it not for Curilla's inspiring fortitude, we wouldn't still be here this day, waging resistance against the Abyssean hordes.
        WITH_HER_HELMING_OUR_DEFENSES_WE_HAD_SUCCESSFULLY                      = 8058,  -- With her helming our defenses, we had successfully repelled the enemy on a number of occasions. But one fateful day, they came at us with such numbers as would make a grown man's bowels turn to water. It was all Curilla could do to buy time for the civilians to flee to safety before she and the soldiers were overwhelmed.
        THINKING_HER_FOREVER_TAKEN_FROM_US_WE_LAMENTED                         = 8059,  -- Thinking her forever taken from us, we lamented the death of a great heroine. So it was to our great joy when we discovered her alive, if severely weakened. She took a grievous wound which left her blind in one eye, but otherwise has been returned to sound physical health.
        BUT_ALAS_ALL_IS_NOT_WELL_WHILE_SHE                                     = 8060,  -- But alas, all is not well. While she is with us in body, the trauma of the ordeal seems to have reft her mind from her. She has no recollection of her own identity, let alone recent events, and will not say so much as a single word to any of us.
        I_SPENT_MANY_A_SLEEPLESS_NIGHT_RESEARCHING_A                           = 8061,  -- I spent many a sleepless night researching a cure for her affliction, and eventually found the knowledge I sought in a tome of healing salvaged from the Kingdom library: a medicine concocted with %. Yet the procurement of this key ingredient eludes me.
        THIS_BRINGS_US_BACK_TO_THE_MATTER_OF                                   = 8062,  -- This brings us back to the matter of my plea. I would have you find the % we need.
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_TOME_OF_HEALING_ARE_REQUIRED                          = 8063,  -- According to the tome of healing, # are required to concoct the medicine.
        FOR_THE_LONGEST_TIME_CURILLA_WAS_THE_BEATING                           = 8064,  -- For the longest time, Curilla was the beating heart of our resistance effort. Bereft of her leadership and military prowess, our defenses may as well be made of clay. Our survival depends on your finding what we need!
        AH_THESE_ARE_THE_I_REQUESTED_SPLENDID                                  = 8065,  -- Ah, these are the % I requested! Splendid!
        USING_THE_SCALES_I_VE_CONCOCTED_THE_WHICH                              = 8066,  -- Using the scales, I've concocted the % which should serve to restore Curilla's memory. Take it and make haste to the northern encampment.
        BEFORE_YOU_GO_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_ACCEPT                                  = 8067,  -- Before you go, I would have you accept this as a token of my gratitude.
        AH_TIS_HEARTENING_TO_SEE_YOU_AGAIN_I                                   = 8068,  -- Ah, 'tis heartening to see you again. I've learned from the tome of healing that % have myriad other applications. Should you come by any more in your journeys, be sure to bring them to me.
        THE_QUIVERS_EVER_SO_SLIGHTLY_BUT_EMITS_NO                              = 8069,  -- The % quivers ever so slightly, but emits no light. There seem to be no monsters in the area.
        THE_QUIVERS_EVER_SO_SLIGHTLY_AND_EMITS_A                               = 8070,  -- The % quivers ever so slightly and emits a faint light. There seem to be no monsters in the immediate vicinity.
        THE_RESONATES_SENDING_A_RADIANT_BEAM_OF_LIGHT                          = 8071,  -- The % resonates [feebly/softly/solidly/strongly/very strongly/furiously], sending a radiant beam of light lancing towards a spot roughly # [yalm/yalms] [east/southeast/south/southwest/west/northwest/north/northeast] of here.
        A_MONSTER_MATERIALIZES_OUT_OF_NOWHERE                                  = 8072,  -- A monster materializes out of nowhere!
        THE_MONSTER_FADES_BEFORE_YOUR_EYES_A_LOOK                              = 8073,  -- The monster fades before your eyes, a look of disappointment on its face.
        THE_TAKES_ON_A_SLIGHTLY_DEEPER_HUE_AND                                 = 8074,  -- The % takes on a slightly deeper hue and becomes %!
        THE_TAKES_ON_A_DEEPER_RICHER_HUE_AND                                   = 8075,  -- The % takes on a deeper, richer hue and becomes %!
        THE_SHATTERS_INTO_TINY_FRAGMENTS                                       = 8076,  -- The % shatters into tiny fragments.
        OBTAINED_KEY_ITEM_2                                                    = 8077,  -- Obtained key item: %!
        THE_MONSTER_FADES_BEFORE_YOUR_EYES_A_LOOK_2                            = 8078,  -- The monster fades before your eyes, a look of disappointment on its face.
        YOU_HAVE_LOST_SIGHT_OF_THE_MONSTER_AND                                 = 8079,  -- You have lost sight of the monster and can no longer sense its presence.
        YOU_HAVE_WANDERED_TOO_FAR_FROM_THE_MONSTER                             = 8080,  -- You have wandered too far from the monster and can no longer sense its presence.
